Package: phoxy
Title: Easily Download, Ingest, and Manipulate the Phoenix Event Dataset
Version: 0.1
Authors@R: as.person("Andy Halterman <ahalterman0@gmail.com> [aut, cre]")
Description: The Phoenix event data set records social and political events
    automatically extracted from news reporting. \code{phoxy} provides
    functions to make acquiring and analyzing this event data easier. For more
    information about Phoenix, see its website here:
    \url{http://phoenixdata.org/} and the website of the Open Event Data
    Alliance here: \url{http://openeventdata.org/}.
Depends: 
    R (>= 3.1.0)
URL: https://github.com/ahalterman/phoxy
LazyData: true
License: MIT
Imports: 
    plyr,
    dplyr,
    rvest,
    stringr,
    RCurl
Suggests: knitr
VignetteBuilder: knitr
RoxygenNote: 6.0.0
